OL,3,CRhun ap Iorwerth set to be chosen as
OL,4,CFirst Minister
OL,6,FLabour's Huw Irranca-Davies, who is
OL,7,Fstill technically deputy first
OL,8,Fminister, has said he intends to put
OL,9,Fhis name forward as the next Llywydd.
OL,11,FFormer Welsh Conservative Leader Paul
OL,12,FDavies has also put his name forward
OL,13,Ffor the role.
OL,15,FHowever, an MS from the governing
OL,16,Fparty must take up either the role of
OL,17,Fthe Llywydd or the deputy, with a
OL,18,Fmember from a different party taking
OL,19,Fup the other.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/8
